Magnificent gardens located below the Palais Galliera. Located very close to the Pont de l'Alma, it is a small peaceful square where the inhabitants of the neighborhood come to rest, as well as a few passing tourists on their way to the Eiffel Tower, nearby on the left bank. At midday, during the week, the square is frequented by office workers, who take advantage of the magic of the place, to have a little picnic on the lawns. The garden is still very well flowered. Very nice and peaceful place.
